comments: I took up to calc in hs and STILL placed math 90 on the entry exam because I never really understood math. I relearned everything in Jodi\'s class, and I actually LOVE it now where before I hated it. She breaks it down, gives you little tricks to use, reviews everything.. and she is very caring (and hilarious) on top of everything. BEST PROFESSOR!!

Jody is a great teacher, if you can keep up and get her quirky personality (which makes her class interesting). She really cares for her students and is helpful if you reach out to her for help. She was pretty easy as well.

Jodi is the worst math instructor I have ever had! She moved too quickly and did not answer questions so that those who are not "good" at math could understand. She is condescending and complains A LOT about being at work. Never checks homework, so you don\'t know if you are even doing the problems right! DON\'T TAKE HER EVER!

Loved her teaching style!She is very clear when she is explaining problems, gives several examples.After every chapter she does group work which helps understand material more.And she always does a Review for every test! They are very helpful and she grades the test right after we turn it in and tells us our grade in the class.I would recommend her

I ABSOLUTELY LOVED HER. SHE WAS QUIRKY AND DOWN TO EARTH AND THE FACT THAT SHE STRUGGLED WITH MATH AT SOME POINT IN HER LIFE, WAS ENCOURAGING TO ME BECUASE SHE RELATED IF I WASN\'T TRACKING. WE NEED MORE INSTRUCTORS LIKE HER.
Loved her! Not too much hw and very easy test. She is on the students side. Learned more than any other math class I\'ve had.
Took her for math 85 and math 90. Awesome teacher. She makes class entertaining and will stay late to help you understand the material. Take her for math!
She made me interested in math.
love her
Amazing teacher. Makes math easy to understand and offers the help you need. Great personality too!

Very clear, gives plenty of examples, provides time for group work so that if you don\'t understand her you can learn from a peer, and goes over homework and questions daily. Pay attention, and do the homework and you should pass with a good grade. I was horrible at math before her, but recieved an A- in her class and actually understand math now!

I loved her!!! i toook her for MATH 075 shes not for everybody, but she made math fun and easy for me... I havent gotten a A+ in math since 2nd grade!!lol she is the best. Test are easy and she doesnt really check to see if you did your homework. Do the work and you will pass with flying colors!!!
NOT HELPFUL AT ALL.
She is a awesome teacher, before i entered into the class i hated math and sucked at it. she made it easy for me, i actually understand it now and enjoy doing my work.
The thing I like most about this instructor is the extreme amount of patience for students an the willingness to make sure that we understand what is taught.
Great teacher. Fun loved comming to class. If you need to take a math class take hers.

BEST TEACHER IVE EVER HAD IN MY LIFE!!!!!!! SHE MADE MY WHOLE YEAR! I HATE EVERYTHING ABOUT MATH. BUT SHE MADE THE WHOLE THING EASY! IT\'S ONE OF THOSE CLASSES THAT\'S A RELIEF TO GO TO, JUST A BREAK FROM THE DAY!
Great teacher helps you understand what you are learning grades tests as soon as you finish. If you need to take math 90 take her. She makes class fun.
Great teacher a must for math.

Awesome teacher, she does expect you to ask questions if you don\'t understand her, but she\'s always willing to help out. I tend to think in the abstract, not helpful with math, but she\'s always there for me. If you can get her for a class, do it. She won\'t disappoint you. She\'s matter of fact, gives you what you need and you figure out the rest
